						<div class="postbody">I'd recommend following Celius (blocks as enemies) if you have only a few things that can be broken like item boxes, or following tokumaru (destruction bitmap, at the cost of not being able to cache a sliding window around the player) if you have huge fields of breakable or collectible things like coins or the bricks of WORLD 1-2 in <em>Super Mario Bros.</em><br /><br />Or just trade programmer time-is-money for replication cost, as the <em>M.C. Kids</em> programmers ended up doing.</div>

